sentences: Taylor Dayne (born Leslie Wunderman; March 7, 1962) is an American singer, songwriter, and actress.
She rose to fame in 1987 after her debut single "Tell It to My Heart".
In December 2016, Billboard magazine ranked her the 28th most successful dance artist of all time.

She began singing solo after finishing college and, under the name Les Lee, recorded two dance singles, "I'm The One You Want" (1985) and "Tell Me Can You Love Me" (1986), which were released on New York indie label Mega Bolt.
